column4: <content>Tower of Babel (Venice) Vendramin Catalogue (ed. Borenius) [= Tancred Borenius (ed.), The Picture Gallery of Andrea Vendramin: The Text of the Original Catalogue, with Reproductions of the Drawings and with Notes, London: Medici Society, 1923]. Scorel.</content>
<part_of.title>Towers of Babel. Reproductions. Towers of Babel by other Artists.</part_of.title>

<parts.title>Neu 20. Alt 15. Turmbau von Babel. Georg Gronau, Venezianische Kunstsammlungen des 16. Jahrhunderts, Jahrbuch für Kunstsammler, IV-V, 1924-25, Frankfurt am Main, 1925, citaat p. 20.</parts.title>

<parts.title>Scorel: Tower of Babel, Cà d'Oro (d. 1562). Here tower reaching into clouds; river on right. The nude figure in foreground Prophet foretelling the doom of Babel?, cf. Isaiah 14 and 47, [dubbel onderstreept] Jeremiah 50f.</parts.title>
<parts.title>F. [Friedrich] Winkler, Jan Scorel oder ""Zuan Fiamengo"", Oud-Holland, 48, 1931, pp. 172-178, citaten pp. 177-178; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. [...]'[scan]</parts.title>
<parts.title>BLES: Turmbau von Babel, Venedig, Akademie, Lit. Burckhardt, Cicerone, p. 805c = Scorel, Cà d'Oro? (früher in kgl. Galerie).</parts.title>

<parts.title>Ad [Addendum] Brueghel [sic]: Babylon. Turm, cf. Marc Anton Michiel (ca. 1525) abgedruckt bei [Theodor von] Frimmel, Beilage der Blätter f[ür] Gemäldekunde, II, Leipzig, Mai 1907, citaat p. 57; [Felix] Becker, Schriftquellen zur Geschichte der altniederländischen Kunst [=Malerei nach den Hauptmeistern chronologisch geordnet], Leipzig [Sellmann & Henne], 1897.</parts.title>
